<item>
            <title>[JDK-8306836] Remove pinned tag for G1 heap regions</title>
                <link>https://bugs.openjdk.org/browse/JDK-8306836</link>
                <project id="10100" key="JDK">JDK</project>
                    <description>There is a &amp;quot;pinned&amp;quot; tag for G1 heap regions to indicate that the region should not move during (young) gc.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
This applies to now removed archive regions and humongous objects.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
With &amp;quot;real&amp;quot; g1 region pinning to better support JNI we need a refcount, a single bit is not sufficient anymore. Further there will be a naming conflict with this feature.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
The (current) pinned flag is surprisingly little used, only for policy decisions.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
The suggestion here is to remove the &amp;quot;pinned&amp;quot; tag as it is, and reserve it for future g1 region pinning (that needs to store that differently).&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
Change current pinned to a plain policy decision method elsewhere.</description>
